<item>
            <title>[LU-1427] lfs find does not find any files in OST after missing OST</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1427</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have in the past removed an OST from lustre.  I drained it, stopped lustre, writeconf everything and fired lustre up without it.  I have not had any issues until today.  When I run lfs find on the OST next in line after the missing OST no files are found.  For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;smuhpc-OST000d_UUID         5.4T        5.3T       85.1G  98% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:13&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST000e_UUID         4.5T        4.4T       82.5G  98% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:14&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST000f_UUID        10.7T        5.2T        5.5T  48% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:15&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST0010_UUID         9.0T        4.5T        4.4T  50% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:16&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST0013_UUID         4.5T        3.8T      674.9G  85% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:19&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST0014_UUID         4.5T      473.8M        4.5T   0% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:20&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST0015_UUID         4.5T      474.1M        4.5T   0% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:21&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
smuhpc-OST0016_UUID         4.5T      474.2M        4.5T   0% /lustre&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:22&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you can see there is a jump between OST0010 and OST0013.  lfs find will not find any files on OST0013.  All files are there and everything else seems to work.  I am able to find files by traversing the file system and runing lfs getstripe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am draining the OSTs to do some work on the underlying hardware.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
